[[Category:Glossary]]
[[Category:OntologySync-managed-resource]]

Freely behaving recordings allow researchers to study neural activity during natural behaviors such as exploration, social interaction, learning, and decision-making. This is a key advantage of the Miniscope platform over traditional two-photon microscopy, which typically requires the animal to be head-fixed.

The lightweight, head-mounted design of the Miniscope is specifically engineered to minimize impact on the animal's natural behavior while recording from hundreds of neurons simultaneously.
